**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Make/Model:** [Insert Vehicle Information]
**Date of Inspection:** [Insert Date]

---

**Location of Damage:**
- The rear fender of the vehicle shows significant damage. There is a noticeable dent and deformation on the lower portion of the fender near the wheel well.

**Type of Damage:**
- The damage appears to be a dent or impact damage. The surface of the fender has been pushed inward, creating a noticeable bulge. The paint has also been disturbed, indicating that the dent extends into the bodywork beneath the surface.

**Additional Observations:**
- The area around the dent seems to have some minor scratches or scuffs, possibly from the impact or handling during the repair process.
- The bumper and the area surrounding the dent appear to be undamaged.

**Conclusion:**
The vehicle has sustained damage to the rear fender. The extent of the damage requires further assessment by a repair professional to determine the appropriate course of action for repairs.
